### RF01/RF02/RF03/RF04/RF06/RF07 — Upload de documento
### POST /api/v1/documents — multipart, role "document:upload" exigida (SecurityConfig).
### Token: rode docs/http/keycloak/01-obter-token.http e cole o access_token abaixo.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8090
@token = COLE_AQUI_O_ACCESS_TOKEN

### Upload aceito (202) — troque o caminho abaixo por um arquivo local válido
### (PDF/JPG/JPEG/PNG/CSV/JSON/XML/TXT/MD — ver app.upload.accepted-types no application.yaml)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="documento.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./caminho/para/seu-arquivo.pdf
--WebAppBoundary--

### Sem token (RF35) — espera 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/documents
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="documento.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./caminho/para/seu-arquivo.pdf
--WebAppBoundary--
